'''Jim Henshaw''' (born [[September 28]], [[1940s#1949|1949]]) is a voice actor who began working during the mid-seventies.

In [[1985]], Henshaw was voicing both one of the [[Wikipedia:Care Bears|Care Bears]] and also [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket Wystri Warrick]] during the first season of [[Ewoks (television series)|''Ewoks'']] TV series. He left ''Ewoks'' for the second season, being replaced with [[Denny Delk]], though he would continue being involved in the Care Bears franchise until 1987.

During the late eighties, he worked as a screenwriter for TV series and movies, including [[Wikipedia:La Femme Nikita|''La Femme Nikita'']] and, during the nineties, he also worked as a TV producer (specially executive producer).

